==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from the French word ''palmier'' for this pastry, ellipsis of [[feuille de palmier]] "palm tree leaf", the original name of this pastry.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A type of [[puff pastry]] [[biscuit]] made in the shape of a [[palm]] leaf and rolled in [[sugar]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|2007|January 30|Lily Koppel|In a Bakery Window, Shades of Miss Havisham|New York Times|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/01/30/nyregion/30ink.html
|passage=Glass cases are filled with a pastel field of pink sweet buns, glossy guava-oozing pastries and their vanilla custard cousins, crispy, heart-shaped orejas (elephant ears, or, at French bakeries, '''palmiers'''), and conchas (shells).}}

